---

An Act to vest certain Lands in the Inhabitants of the Portobello Road District.

BE IT ENACTED by the General Assembly of New Zealand in Parliament assembled, and by the authority of the same, as follows:---

##### 1 Short Title
    
*   This Act may be cited as the Portobello Road District Lands Vesting Act 1911\.

##### 2 Lands in Schedule vested in road district
    
*   The lands described in the Schedule to this Act are hereby vested in the Corporation of the Inhabitants of the Portobello Road District, and the District Land Registrar of the Otago Land Registration District shall accordingly, on the application of the Portobello Road Board, issue a certificate or certificates of title for the said lands to the said Corporation.

##### 3 Board may reclaim lands on being authorized
    
*   Nothing herein shall be deemed to prevent the reclamation of the said lands, or any part or parts thereof, if and when such reclamation shall be authorized in manner provided by the Harbours Amendment Act 1910, or any other Act for the time being in force relating to the reclamation of land from the sea.

##### 4 Act to be deemed special Act
    
*   This Act shall be deemed to be a special Act within the meaning of the Harbours Act 1950\.
    
    The reference to the Harbours Act 1923 was substituted, as from 1 January 1924, for a reference to the Harbours Act 1908 pursuant to section 259 Harbours Act 1923 (1923 No 40). That reference was in turn substituted, as from 15 October 1950, for a reference to the Harbours Act 1950 pursuant to section 269(1) Harbours Act 1950\.

---

## Schedule

ALL that parcel of land, containing by admeasurement 1 acre 1 rood 26 perches, more or less, situated in Macandrew Bay, in the Otago Harbour, being portion of the foreshore fronting Section 18, Upper Harbour East District: commencing at a point distant from the south-west corner of Section 20, Upper Harbour East District, 1303 links, bearing 326° 30′ NW; 842.2 links, bearing 21° 30′ NE; 252.5 links, bearing 81° 24′ NE: bounded towards the east by high-water mark; towards the north by high-water mark; towards the west by a public road; and towards the south by high-water mark to commencing-point.

Also all that parcel of land, containing by admeasurement 1 acre 1 rood 24 perches, more or less, situated in Latham Bay, in the Otago Harbour, being portion of the foreshore adjoining road fronting Section 1, Block VII, Portobello Bay District: commencing at a point distant from Trig K 1, 506.8 links, bearing 98° 32′ 30″ SE; 305.4 links, bearing 32° 0′ 7″ NE; 490.9 links, bearing 103° 41′ SE; 256.6 links, bearing 131° 12′ SE; 585 links, bearing 179° 22′ SE: bounded towards the south-east by high-water mark; towards the north-east by a public road: towards the west by high-water mark to commencing-point.

